<subSubSection id="C36D6511FFE7FFCFFF3B759AD2F2F99E" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC8369AFFE7FFCFFF3B759AD2F2F99E" blockId="31.[151,1437,1481,1759]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
REMARKS.—This is the largest of the Ecuadorian 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D19FFE7FFCFFD6F759AD32EFA2D" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[707,830,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903EA88FFE7FFCFFD6F759AD32EFA2D" box="[707,830,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with body lengths of about 
<quantity id="4C8F9B7FFFE7FFCFFB777599D53BFA2A" box="[1243,1323,1481,1508]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="48.0">48 mm</quantity>
and wing spans of more than 
<quantity id="4C8F9B7FFFE7FFCFFEC175BDD1DCF9C6" box="[365,460,1517,1544]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="120.0">120 mm</quantity>
. The basic brown and piceous coloration, the anterior extension of the postclypeus when viewed from the dorsal side and the fore wings have infuscation on the radial and radiomedial crossveins which easily distinguish it from 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D19FFE7FFCFFE197666D2CEF99E" authority="Goding, 1925" authorityName="Goding" authorityYear="1925" box="[437,734,1589,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis id="B903EA88FFE7FFCFFE197666D22AF981" box="[437,570,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">M. truncata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE64B6BFFE7FFCFFDED7665D2CEF99E" author="Goding, F. W." box="[577,734,1589,1616]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref70044" refString="Goding, F. W. (1925) Synopsis of the Cicadidae of Ecuador. Revista del Colegio Nacional Rocafuerte, 7, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1925">Goding, 1925</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36D6511FFE7FFCFFF6B760AD17AF911" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC8369AFFE7FFCFFF6B760AD17AF911" blockId="31.[151,1437,1481,1759]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
DISTRIBUTION.—The species is known from 
<collectingCountry id="F360760AFFE7FFCFFD077609D2E2F9BD" box="[683,754,1625,1651]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F360760AFFE7FFCFFD517609D37EF9BD" box="[765,878,1625,1651]" name="Colombia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F360760AFFE7FFCFFCD57609D3C8F9BD" box="[889,984,1625,1651]" name="Ecuador" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F360760AFFE7FFCFFC4E7609D49AF9BD" box="[994,1162,1625,1651]" name="French Guiana" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F360760AFFE7FFCFFB387609D51AF9BD" box="[1172,1290,1625,1651]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F360760AFFE7FFCFFAE8760AD58DF9BA" box="[1348,1437,1626,1652]" name="Panama" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE64B6BFFE7FFCFFF33762DD155F959" author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[159,325,1661,1687]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref71633" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
; Sanborn 2011a; 2013; 2018c; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE64B6BFFE7FFCFFD36762ED345F959" author="Maes, J. - M. &amp; Moulds, M. &amp; Sanborn, A. F." box="[666,853,1661,1688]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref71321" refString="Maes, J. - M., Moulds, M. &amp; Sanborn, A. F. (2012) Cicadidae (Homoptera) de Nicaragua: catalogo ilustrado, incluyendo especies exoticas del Museo Entomologico de Leon. Revista Nicaraguense Entomologia, 72 (Suplemento 2), 1 - 138." type="journal article" year="2012">
Maes 
<emphasis id="B903EA88FFE7FFCFFD70762ED303F959" box="[732,787,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE64B6BFFE7FFCFFCF2762DD449F959" author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Maes, J. - M." box="[862,1113,1661,1688]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="437 - 442" refId="ref74898" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Maes, J. - M. (2012) Checklist of the cicadas (Insecta: Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Nicaragua including new records for seventeen species. Check List, 8, 437 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 8.3.437" type="journal article" year="2012">Sanborn &amp; Maes 2012</bibRefCitation>
) with recent records reported for 
<collectingCountry id="F360760AFFE7FFCFFF1376F2D0E2F972" box="[191,242,1698,1724]" name="Peru" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE64B6BFFE7FFCFFEAD76F1D1A2F972" author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[257,434,1697,1724]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 129" refId="ref74088" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2020 b) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Peru including the descriptions of twenty-four new species, three new synonymies, and thirty-seven new records. Zootaxa, 4785 (1), 1 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4785.1.1" type="journal article" year="2020">Sanborn 2020b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE64B6BFFE7FFCFFE6976F1D27BF972" author="Goding, F. W." box="[453,619,1697,1724]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref70044" refString="Goding, F. W. (1925) Synopsis of the Cicadidae of Ecuador. Revista del Colegio Nacional Rocafuerte, 7, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1925">Goding (1925)</bibRefCitation>
reported the species from Posorja, Guayas province and Macas, Morona Santiago province.
</paragraph>
